==2004 Parliamentary General Election==
In the [[Sri Lankan legislative election, 2004|2 April 2004 election]] in which the [[Sri Lanka Freedom Party|SLFP]] and [[Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna|JVP]] alliance led by President Kumaratunga came to power, the TNA led by R. Sampanthan won 6.9% of the popular vote and 22 out of 225 seats in the [[Sri Lankan parliament]].

